<plot>"The Open Road: America Looks at Aging" is a road trip across America that explores what is going to happen when America's 77 million Baby Boomers retire. The film explores both the personal opportunities and obstacles to a successful "Third Stage of Life," as well as what the policy and economic issues that will confront America as it approaches this tidal wave of retirees.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?580477</url></doc>
